					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>170 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>180</height>
										<width>140</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>135</height>
										<width>80</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>170 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaf and 4 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>17 quires of 10 leaves each, signed with Hebrew letters on the first and last page.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="25" writtenLines="25">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible plummet ruling (on each bifolio) and pricking.</p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side of the folios distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Last line written within the ruling.</p>
									<p>Some marginal notes in semi-cursive script. </p>
									<p>Sections numbered in Hebrew letters in the margins.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script of the 15th century, unpunctuated. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Several ownership notes: folios 1r, 1v, 169v, 170r.</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Dominico Irosolomitano</name>, Italian censor (active in the last quarter of the 16th and first quarter of the 17th century): inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1597</date> (folio 168v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">61</ref>, and appendix § 62-74.
</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Giovanni Domenico Carretto</name>, Italian censor (active in the first quarter of the 17th century): inscribed with his name, (folio 168v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">100-101</ref>, and appendix § 80-84. </p>
						</additions>
